Assessment of corticosteroid treatment of ethionine pancreatitis in the rabbit. Corticosteroid treatment of acute pancreatitis has recently been advocated by clinicians. The effectiveness of steroids in the prevention of pancreatitis was studied in the model of ethionine pancreatitis in rabbits. A group of 20 rabbits received ethionine for 6 days. Methyl prednisolone succinate was also given to half of the group for a period of 6 days. Animals were killed on the 7th day enzyme determinations were done